data.title: Let it Fly Show
data.text:
Mike'l is joined by Creighton Women's Basketball star and Team USA 3x3 forward Morgan Maly. Morgan joins Mike'l before she departs for practice and preparation for this year's Olympics in Paris with Team USA's 3x3 team. Mike'l and Morgan discuss her acceptance to this year's team, what she's looking forward to the most from this experience, what she likes most about 3x3 compared to 5v5, goals for next season's Creighton Women's Basketball team, her personal goals on the court, Â games she looks forward to the most in the Big East, and the perfect dinner date! Mike'l also covers the biggest debate in basketball right now, Caitlin Clark or Angel Reese for WNBA Rookie of the Year.

Mike'l and Josh are joined by former Creighton star and new Boston Celtics player Baylor Scheierman, immediately after he gets drafted in the first round with the 30th pick by the Celtics. Baylor is coming off an incredible season for the Creighton Bluejays, earning third-team All-American honors. He also had a historic season statistically, breaking records for points, rebounds, and assists in Creighton's history. He had a fantastic summer of workouts and combines that saw his stock rise even higher with some NBA teams. Last night, he was drafted into the NBA by the Boston Celtics in the first round! The guys discuss what it feels like to be drafted, Baylor's journey, Baylor's parents, playing for the Boston Celtics, Coach McDermott, and more!

Mike'l and Josh are joined by Nebraska Huskers and Green Bay Packers star running back Ahman Green. The guys discuss Ahman's career playing for the Packers, his time as the star running back for the Huskers, the 95' and 97' national championships, his current job as the esports coach and teacher at the University of Nebraska-Lincoln, e-gaming, horror movies, and his favorite video games. Mike'l and Josh also discuss the NBA Finals and all the top stories of the week.
